==English==

===Pronunciation===
*: {{rhymes|æʃ}}

===Etymology===
From Old Norse, akin to Swedish ''basa'' 'to baste, whip, lash, flog', Danish ''baske'' 'to beat, strike, cudgel'.

===Verb===
{{en-verb|bash|es}}

# To [[violent]]ly [[pound]] [[downward]] with one's [[fist]]s.
#: ''The thugs kept '''bashing''' the [[cower]]ing victim.''
# To [[criticize]] [[harsh]]ly.
#: ''He '''bashed''' my [[idea]]s.''
# {{context|Internet colloq.}} To submit to [http://bash.org Bash.org], or [http://qdb.us/ QDB].
# To [[strike]] heavily.
#: ''He '''bashed''' himself against the door.''
# To [[collide]].
#: ''Don't '''bash''' into me with that [[shopping trolley]].''

